From: PureCloak Authors <purecloak-dev@purecloak.org>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 19:00:00 +0800
Subject: Replace ICE candidate IP at allocator level for anti-fingerprinting

Adds a second layer of IP spoofing in BasicPortAllocatorSession::
OnCandidateReady(), which is called when each port signals a new
candidate. After the candidate is sanitized by the allocator, PureCloak
replaces the IP address with the spoofed value from
--fingerprint-webrtc-ip if configured.

This complements the Port::AddAddress() level spoofing (patch #49) by
providing defense-in-depth at the allocator level. Together these ensure
that even if a port creates candidates through a different code path,
the IP is still spoofed before being signaled to the application.

Only host candidates (is_local()) are spoofed to preserve the
functionality of STUN/TURN relay candidates.

---
 third_party/webrtc/p2p/client/basic_port_allocator.cc | 18 +++++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 17 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/third_party/webrtc/p2p/client/basic_port_allocator.cc b/third_party/webrtc/p2p/client/basic_port_allocator.cc
--- a/third_party/webrtc/p2p/client/basic_port_allocator.cc
+++ b/third_party/webrtc/p2p/client/basic_port_allocator.cc
@@ -55,6 +55,12 @@
 #include "rtc_base/strings/string_builder.h"
 #include "rtc_base/trace_event.h"
 
+// PureCloak: ICE candidate IP spoofing for anti-fingerprinting
+#include "purecloak/common/buildflags.h"
+#if BUILDFLAG(IS_PURECLOAK)
+#include "purecloak/common/purecloak_seed.h"
+#endif
+
 namespace webrtc {
 namespace {
 
@@ -992,7 +998,19 @@ void BasicPortAllocatorSession::OnCandidateReady(Port* port,
 
   if (data->ready() && CheckCandidateFilter(c)) {
     std::vector<Candidate> candidates;
-    candidates.push_back(allocator_->SanitizeCandidate(c));
+    Candidate sanitized = allocator_->SanitizeCandidate(c);
+#if BUILDFLAG(IS_PURECLOAK)
+    // PureCloak: replace real IP with spoofed value from --fingerprint-webrtc-ip
+    if (sanitized.is_local()) {
+      const auto& spoofed_ip =
+          purecloak::PureCloakSeed::GetInstance()->webrtc_ip();
+      if (!spoofed_ip.empty()) {
+        SocketAddress spoofed_addr(spoofed_ip, sanitized.address().port());
+        sanitized.set_address(spoofed_addr);
+      }
+    }
+#endif
+    candidates.push_back(sanitized);
     NotifyCandidatesReady(this, candidates);
   } else {
     RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Discarding candidate because it doesn't match filter.";
